description: Returns a list of the available engines.

parameters.name: EngineVersion
parameters.description: The database engine version to return. Example: 3.6.0

parameters.name: DBParameterGroupFamily
parameters.description: The name of a specific parameter group family to return details for. Constraints: If provided, must match an existing DBParameterGroupFamily.

parameters.name: Filters
parameters.description: This parameter is not currently supported. (dict) --- A named set of filter values, used to return a more specific list of results. You can use a filter to match a set of resources by specific criteria, such as IDs. Wildcards are not supported in filters. The name of the filter. Filter names are case sensitive. One or more filter values. Filter values are case sensitive. (string) ---

nested_params.name: Name
nested_params.description: The name of the filter. Filter names are case sensitive.

nested_params.name: Values
nested_params.description: One or more filter values. Filter values are case sensitive.

parameters.name: MaxRecords
parameters.description: The maximum number of records to include in the response. If more records exist than the specified MaxRecords value, a pagination token (marker) is included in the response so that the remaining results can be retrieved. Default: 100 Constraints: Minimum 20, maximum 100.

nested_items.name: Marker
nested_items.description: An optional pagination token provided by a previous request. If this parameter is specified, the response includes only records beyond the marker, up to the value specified by MaxRecords.

nested_items.name: DBEngineVersions
nested_items.description: Detailed information about one or more engine versions.

nested_items.name: Engine
nested_items.description: The name of the database engine.

nested_items.name: EngineVersion
nested_items.description: The version number of the database engine.

nested_items.name: DBParameterGroupFamily
nested_items.description: The name of the parameter group family for the database engine.

nested_items.name: DBEngineDescription
nested_items.description: The description of the database engine.

nested_items.name: DBEngineVersionDescription
nested_items.description: The description of the database engine version.

nested_items.name: ValidUpgradeTarget
nested_items.description: A list of engine versions that this database engine version can be upgraded to.

nested_items.name: Engine
nested_items.description: The name of the upgrade target database engine.

nested_items.name: EngineVersion
nested_items.description: The version number of the upgrade target database engine.

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: The version of the database engine that an instance can be upgraded to.

nested_items.name: AutoUpgrade
nested_items.description: A value that indicates whether the target version is applied to any source DB instances that have AutoMinorVersionUpgrade set to true.

nested_items.name: IsMajorVersionUpgrade
nested_items.description: A value that indicates whether a database engine is upgraded to a major version.

nested_items.name: ExportableLogTypes
nested_items.description: The types of logs that the database engine has available for export to Amazon CloudWatch Logs.

nested_items.name: SupportsLogExportsToCloudwatchLogs
nested_items.description: A value that indicates whether the engine version supports exporting the log types specified by ExportableLogTypes to CloudWatch Logs.

nested_items.name: SupportedCACertificateIdentifiers
nested_items.description: A list of the supported CA certificate identifiers.

nested_items.name: SupportsCertificateRotationWithoutRestart
nested_items.description: Indicates whether the engine version supports rotating the server certificate without rebooting the DB instance.
